## 🌱 GitHub Skills Showcase

You can optionally verify courses you've completed in GitHub Skills, such as *Introduction to Secret Scanning*, *Release-Based Workflow*, etc. Those badges can be included here similarly to how **Oghenesuvwe‑dev** highlights their DevOps journey.:contentReference[oaicite:1]{index=1}  

---

## ✅ How to Customize

1. Replace placeholders: `YOUR_USERNAME`, `youremail@example.com`, and project names.
2. Generate badges from [GitHub Readme Stats](https://github.com/anuraghazra/github-readme-stats) and plug them in.
3. If you’ve done GitHub Skills or other learning paths, add them in a **“Skills Showcase”** section.
4. Save as `README.md` in your profile repo (`yourusername/yourusername`).

